<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1435,521,823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,557,580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head anteriorly triangularly produced, median and lateral margins strongly carinate, color black with offwhite or red markings on head and apex of scutellum, forewing claval veins separate throughout length, male pygofer with long ventral process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1435,521,823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,661,684]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Remarks.</emphasis>
So far, eight known species are included in 
<taxonomicName authority="Melichar. Two" authorityName="Melichar. Two" box="[787,1055,660,684]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[787,892,660,684]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Pythamus</emphasis>
Melichar. Two
</taxonomicName>
of them, 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker" authorityName="Baker" box="[1159,1363,660,684]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus">
<emphasis box="[1159,1291,660,684]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">P. productus</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[1299,1363,661,684]" name="United States Pacific Island Wildlife Refuges" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Baker</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker" authorityName="Baker" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decoratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">P. decoratus</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[265,330,696,719]" name="United States Pacific Island Wildlife Refuges" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Baker</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
, known only from females, are uncertain in their placement (
<bibRefCitation author="Wei" box="[1000,1172,695,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" refString="Wei, C., Webb, M. D. &amp; Zhang, Y. (2014) Identity of Baker's species described in the Oriental leafhopper genus Pythamus (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae) with description of a new genus. Zootaxa, 3795 (3), 289 - 300. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3795.3.4" type="journal article" year="2014">
Wei 
<emphasis box="[1053,1102,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">et al</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[1117,1172,696,719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and another species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Webb" authorityName="Li &amp; Webb" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnama">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">P. vietnama</emphasis>
Li &amp; Webb
</taxonomicName>
, was also described based only on females. 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang" authorityName="Huang" box="[875,1140,729,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Riseveinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiabaotawow">
<emphasis box="[875,1059,729,753]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">P. chiabaotawow</emphasis>
Huang
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Li" authorityName="Li" box="[151,295,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Riseveinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,265,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Riseveinus</emphasis>
Li
</taxonomicName>
in this study. These four species are excluded from the following key.
</paragraph>
